docs.lead_paragraph: The emotional problems of college students have been getting much attention--but usually the focus is on academic failures, drug addiction, excessive drinking and sexual experimentation. Last week, a new study put the spotlight on increasing campus suicides.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Oct. 8--A crucial stage has been reached in the most massive study ever attempted of the factors that affect early human birth and development.

headline.main: Massive Study of Birth Defects at Crucial Stage

docs.abstract: Massive study by Natl Inst of Neurological Diseases in collaboration with major hosps, begun 7 yrs ago, enters final stage but has at least 7 more yrs to run; 60,000 pregnancies and resultant children studied; details
